A vast digital graveyard at twilight, rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures and warm amber lighting. Ancient stone tombstones are shaped like old computer monitors and server towers, weathered and covered in moss and climbing vines. From one cracked monitor-tombstone, delicate streams of glowing data particles rise like fireflies, transforming mid-air into elegant origami paper cranes that flutter toward a distant peaceful lake. The lake's surface reflects a starry sky and shimmers with swirling layers of translucent documents stacked like sediment. A small fox spirit sits among the tombstones, watching the transformation with gentle curiosity. Cherry blossom petals drift through the scene, mixing with the luminous data streams. Rolling hills covered in tall grass frame the background, with a single ancient tree silhouetted against a gradient sky of deep purple and soft orange.
